(27, 27, NULL, 'Add columns for first name, middle name and surname in #__users table', 'Splitting the #__users table name column into 3 columns (first name, middle name and surname) will simplify lot of use cases where you don''t want to get the users full real name. Post processing the name will result in a flawed result since you can''t predict with 100% accuracy how the name is composed.\r<br>\r<br>E.g. a mail form where you want to address the person "Hi, James \\n\\n Just for today we have a special offer...".\r<br>\r<br>http://ideas.joomla.org/forums/84261-joomla-idea-pool/suggestions/1241451-name', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-05 07:36:26', '2011-12-05 07:42:57', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(28, 28, NULL, 'Add columns for first name, middle name and surname in #__users table', 'Splitting the #__users table name column into 3 columns (first name, middle name and surname) will simplify lot of use cases where you don''t want to get the users full real name. Post processing the name will result in a flawed result since you can''t predict with 100% accuracy how the name is composed.\r<br>\r<br>E.g. a mail form where you want to address the person "Hi, James \\n\\n Just for today we have a special offer...".\r<br>\r<br>http://ideas.joomla.org/forums/84261-joomla-idea-pool/suggestions/1241451-name\r<br>\r<br>Will also require some changes to the platform as well (are included in this pull request).\r<br>\r<br>I hope I touched all the places the name field is used.', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-05 07:40:29', '2011-12-05 15:45:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/28.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(29, 29, 27221, '[#27221] Improvements for batch processing', 'This is the pull request coinciding with http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=27221.\r<br>\r<br>This improves the batch processing throughout the CMS for Joomla! 2.5.  Included in this pull request:\r<br>\r<br>- All components: Improved ACL checks for create and edit permissions\r<br>- com_banners: Full batch processing implementation (category, language, and client)\r<br>- com_contact: Full batch processing implementation (access, category, language, and linked user)\r<br>- com_content: Handles featured articles during copy process (see \r<br>- com_modules: Full batch processing implementation (access, copy/move between positions, language)\r<br>- com_newsfeeds: Full batch processing implementation (access, category, and language)\r<br>- com_users: Implement unused batch processing code for group assignment\r<br>\r<br>This item also references CMS issues [#26905] and [#26986].\r<br>\r<br>One TODO item remains as of this time: Implementing batch processing logic for menu associations (I''ve been looking at this, and hope to have something ready soon)\r<br>\r<br>Also, to assist with conforming to coding standards, in many of the files that I''ve edited, I''ve applied the coding standard from the Platform into my edited files.\r<br>\r<br>This change edits several library files as well; a separate pull request for the Platform is forthcoming.', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-05 12:12:08', '2012-01-03 08:17:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/29.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(30, 30, NULL, 'User Notes', 'This patch adds the ability to attach notes to a user.\r<br>\r<br>Adds:\r<br>* User notes list view and edit page.\r<br>* User notes categories\r<br>* Registered date filter to list view\r<br>\r<br>The patch also modifies the main user list. In a new site, there will be an "Add Note" icon against each user.  This will link to a note edit form where you can add a note with a subject, description, category and review date.\r<br>\r<br>When notes are added to a user the main user list shows two more icons: an icon that links to a modal popup summary of the notes, and an icon to jump to the full notes list filtering on that user.\r<br>\r<br>Feature tracker reference: http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemBrowse&tracker_id=8549', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-06 10:08:37', '2011-12-18 23:03:45', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/30.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(31, 31, NULL, 'Manager for Language Overrides', 'Hi,\r<br>\r<br>while supporting our component we come often across people who want to change the language output.\r<br>It has to be explained then in which file the string can be found so that it can be edited.\r<br>\r<br>With the new version of Joomla! it is possible to create language overrides so that the changes aren''t lost anymore during the updates. This is great, but the user still has to find the correct language file in order to detect which language constant he has to override.\r<br>\r<br>With this pull request I''d like to suggest a new manager which simplifies that.\r<br>It''s a new tab in language manager in which users can create language overrides for any installed language.\r<br>\r<br>In the edit view a search can be done for language strings the user wants to change. The script will then take completely care of the override.ini files.\r<br>\r<br>This way people can change any language output of their site without having to know anything about language constants or override.ini files.\r<br>\r<br>Please let me know what you think about that.\r<br>\r<br>Regards\r<br>Chraneco', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-06 20:55:21', '2012-01-18 15:59:26', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/31.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(32, 32, NULL, 'Bug fix 1.7.3: SQL error when saving a module', 'Saving a module produces an SQL error due to incorrect usage of the query builder.  JDatabaseQuery::values takes a whole tuple of values or an array of tuples (which differs from the columns method which can add to the list of columns with subsequent calls).\r<br>\r<br>Patch also adds some other common files to .gitignore.\r<br>\r<br>NOTE: Error is occurring against the master git platform, not Joomla''s copy of `/libraries/joomla/`.', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-08 09:42:36', '2011-12-12 00:42:08', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/32.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
