(41, 41, NULL, 'Added a new link on the module manager page to add a module for that menutype', 'Solution for:\r<br>http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=27379\r<br>\r<br>This code is actually pretty neat because it allows you to pre-populate any module parameter when creating a new module.  Could have a wealth of other applications.\r<br>\r<br>Test plan:\r<br>1. Add a new menu type\r<br>2. Check that this link appears in the menu manager list against the new menu "**Add a module for this menu type."\r<br>3. Click link and ensure you go to a new menu page and the menutype is populated.  Save and check details.\r<br>4. Create other modules and edit other modules and ensure the "menutype" behaves as expected.', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-14 23:01:58', '2011-12-16 21:16:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/41.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(42, 42, NULL, 'Wrong context for ''continue''', 'In the rare case that a content plugin returns false from the onContentBeforeSave event when creating a new folder in the media manager, we should return false rather than ''continue'' which can only be used inside loops anyway. ', 3, 0, 10, '2011-12-16 08:09:56', '2011-12-20 03:41:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/42.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
