(101, 101, NULL, 'Code style: Let''s start', 'This is an attempt to bring the CMS coding standards in line with the Joomla! platform.\r<br>I believe that this is going to be a long way, so this is the first baby step ;)\r<br>This will:\r<br>\r<br>* Add a phing build.xml file containing the code sniffer commands and the CMS fileset.\r<br>* Add the ruleset.xml from the platform. Some generic sniffs have not been included (yet).\r<br>* Add the first custom Joomla! Coding standard sniff (Joomla_Sniffs_WhiteSpace_DisallowSpaceIndentSniff).\r<br>* Fix the PHP code according to the present rules.\r<br>\r<br>List of used sniffs (8):\r<br>\r<br>* Joomla_Sniffs_WhiteSpace_DisallowSpaceIndentSniff\r<br>* PEAR_Sniffs_NamingConventions_ValidClassNameSniff\r<br>* PEAR_Sniffs_Classes_ClassDeclarationSniff\r<br>* PEAR_Sniffs_Commenting_InlineCommentSniff\r<br>* Generic_Sniffs_Files_LineEndingsSniff\r<br>* PEAR_Sniffs_Formatting_MultiLineAssignmentSniff\r<br>* Generic_Sniffs_NamingConventions_UpperCaseConstantNameSniff\r<br>* Generic_Sniffs_PHP_DisallowShortOpenTagSniff\r<br>\r<br>Most common errors:\r<br>\r<br>* Class names have to start with an upper case letter, the opening brace must be on a new line.\r<br>* Spaces were used for indenting instead of tabs.\r<br>* Windows line endings instead of Unix.\r<br>\r<br>I hope this will continue and being used before merging pull requests or applying patches.\r<br>\r<br>joomlacode.org bug tracker: [#27837](http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_item_id=27837)', 3, 0, 10, '2012-01-25 05:20:55', '2012-07-29 06:53:36', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/101.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(102, 102, NULL, 'Article layout improvments', 'Removing unnecessary div around article image.\r<br>Improving code formatting for better readability and consistency.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-01-25 15:36:56', '2012-02-03 14:23:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/102.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(103, 103, NULL, 'Update no longer purges after each update, allowing multiple updates to run', 'Currently the update process purges the update table after every update. This means the updates are limited to one at a time, since the table is purged, and forces the updates to be refetched multiple times if multiple extensions need to be updated.\r<br>\r<br>This change will only delete the specific row from the update table that was just installed instead of purging the entire table.', 3, 0, 10, '2012-01-25 21:52:13', '2012-02-04 06:42:27', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/103.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
