(109, 109, NULL, 'Module Weblinks Problem and the Solutions.', '===============================================================================================\r<br>Module Weblinks Problem\r<br>And the Solutions\r<br>31 January 2012\r<br>================================================================================================\r<br>\r<br>1.	DIRECTION\r<br>------------------------\r<br>	Please open:\r<br>	Administrator->Extensions->Module Manager->Weblinks\r<br>\r<br>2.	PROBLEM\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>	This Mudule (mod_weblinks) displays Website Links.\r<br>	But an error occure when we want to record how many times the links has been clicked.\r<br>	The destination links will error, because the link not found when searched in MySQL Database.\r<br>\r<br>	When in Mudule, Count Clicks setting up to "No", then no problem, the link will be found,\r<br>	but when Count Clicks set to "Yes", then this problem appears.\r<br>\r<br>	For testing puspose, please set Count Clicks to Yes, then Joomla! should record the clicking.\r<br>	And Target Window to "Open in a new window", Description to "Hide" and Hits to "Show".\r<br>	Then publish a Weblink Module to the Front-end. Then click any link as you want.\r<br>	Then there is a problem comes, Joomla! can not find the URL. Error message: "Web link not found".\r<br>	Please look at attached file: "Preview-1.jpg".\r<br>	Joomla! can not bring you to destination URL because the destination URL address can not be found.\r<br>	How come the URL can not be found, because Joomla! can not find the URL.\r<br>	How come Joomla! can not find the URL, because there are some error code in Weblinks Module.\r<br>\r<br>	For example, the wrong URL (Please look at attached file: "Preview-1.jpg"):\r<br>	http://localhost/index.php/component/weblinks/?task=weblink.go&catid=&id=32:joomla-specific-links\r<br>\r<br>	It should be (Please look at attached file: "Preview-2.jpg"):\r<br>	http://localhost/index.php/component/weblinks/?task=weblink.go&catid=32&id=5\r<br>\r<br>	The wrong code:\r<br>	*	Can not find Weblinks Category ID (catid), so catid has empty Varible.\r<br>	*	Variable id (Link ID) contains wrong data, it cointains Weblinks Category ID (catid)\r<br>\r<br>3.	SOLUTION\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>3.1	=== Stage 1 of 3 ===\r<br>	Open file that have error in scripts.\r<br>	Please one File helper.php, at: http://localhost/modules/mod_weblinks/helper.php\r<br>	Go to line: 91.\r<br>\r<br>3.2	=== Stage 2 of 3 ===\r<br>	Change Variable "$item->catslug" into "$item->catid".\r<br>\r<br>3.3	=== Stage 3 of 3 ===\r<br>	Change Variable "$item->slug" into "$item->id".\r<br>	(Please look at attached file: "Preview-3.jpg")\r<br>\r<br>	Done!\r<br>	Our Module should run smoothly at the Front-End.\r<br>\r<br>4.	TESTING ENVIRONMENT\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>	*	Joomla! 2.5.0 Stable [ Ember ] 24-Jan-2012 14:00 GMT\r<br>	*	Internet Browser: Chrome 16.0.912.75\r<br>	*	ApacheFriends XAMPP version 1.7.7\r<br>	*	Apache 2.2.21\r<br>	*	MySQL 5.5.16 (Community Server)\r<br>	*	PHP 5.3.8 (VC9 X86 32bit thread safe) + PEAR\r<br>\r<br>================================================================================================', 3, 0, 1, '2012-01-31 10:55:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/109.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(110, 110, NULL, 'Update modules/mod_related_items/helper.php', '===============================================================================================\r<br>Module Articles - Related Articles Problem\r<br>And the Solutions\r<br>31 January 2012\r<br>================================================================================================\r<br>\r<br>1.	INSTRUCTION\r<br>------------------------\r<br>	Please open:\r<br>	Administrator->Extensions->Module Manager->Module Articles - Related Articles\r<br>\r<br>2.	PROBLEM\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>	This Mudule (mod_related_items) searching for related article items based on Meta Keywords.\r<br>	But an error occure when we want to showing the Module at the Front-end.\r<br>	The Mudule does not show up at all because there are some scripts error in our File.\r<br>\r<br>	For testing puspose, please create Article 1, Article 2, and Article 3,\r<br>	with same Meta Keywords: ABC, DEF, GHI. The results should be as following:\r<br>\r<br>	*	Article 1 should display Article 2 and Article 3.\r<br>	*	Article 2 should display Article 1 and Article 3.\r<br>	*	Article 3 should display Article 1 and Article 2.\r<br>\r<br>	Then try to publish the module at the Front-end.\r<br>	Then we will get our Module does not show up at all.\r<br>	We only get empty space.\r<br>\r<br>3.	SOLUTION\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>3.1	=== Stage 1 of 4 ===\r<br>	Open file that have error in scripts.\r<br>	Please one File helper.php, at: http://localhost/modules/mod_related_items/helper.php\r<br>	Go to line: 98.\r<br>\r<br>3.2	=== Stage 2 of 4 ===\r<br>	Remove Unnecessary "$concat_string" Variable.\r<br>	Description:\r<br>	It is not necessary to use concatenate function around here.\r<br>	Because what we need is a Variable contains "a.metakey" only.\r<br>	As additional information, term "concatenate" is not registered in both MySQL and PHP.\r<br>	The function "concatenate" does not exist!.\r<br>	The registered function that existed in MySQL is: "CONCAT",\r<br>	so be aware that we must use "CONCAT" rather "concatenate".\r<br>	Also, present REPLACE Syntax for MySQL query not necessary at all.\r<br>	It is enough create a Variable contains "a.metakey" only.\r<br>	So, remove this $concat_string Variable and the rest.\r<br>	//$concat_string = $query->concatenate(array('','', ''REPLACE(a.metakey, ", ", ",")'', '',''));\r<br>\r<br>3.3	=== Stage 3 of 4 ===\r<br>	Create New Variable.\r<br>	Description:\r<br>	We are free to create or not create a new Variable that contains data: "a.metakey" only.\r<br>	Since we already have "a.metakey" that fulfill our needs.\r<br>	Here we create a Varible that contains data: "a.metakey".\r<br>	"a.metakey" refers to "metakey" field in "#__content" table.\r<br>	This new Variable is the newest of $concat_string Variable.\r<br>	$FieldMetaKey=''a.metakey'';\r<br>\r<br>3.4	=== Stage 4 of 4 ===\r<br>	Description:\r<br>	Remove Error Code and Repair It with Replace It with the True Code.\r<br>	These scripts have some errors. This make the Module at Front-End does not show-up.\r<br>	//$query->where(''(''.$concat_string.'' LIKE "%''.implode(''%" OR ''.$concat_string.'' LIKE "%'', $likes).''%")'');\r<br>	//$query->where(''(''.$FieldMetaKey.'' LIKE "%''.implode(''%" OR ''.$concat_string.'' LIKE "%'', $likes).''%")'');\r<br>	These are the newest scripts.\r<br>	Our Module will run smoothly at Front-End. "$.FieldMetaKey" and "'' LIKE " was removed.\r<br>	$query->where(''(''.$FieldMetaKey.'' LIKE "%''.implode(''%" OR ''.''"%'', $likes).''%")'');\r<br>\r<br>	Done.\r<br>	Our Module should run smoothly at the Front-End.\r<br>\r<br>4.	TESTING ENVIRONMENT\r<br>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r<br>	*	Joomla! 2.5.0 Stable [ Ember ] 24-Jan-2012 14:00 GMT\r<br>	*	Internet Browser: Chrome 16.0.912.75\r<br>	*	ApacheFriends XAMPP version 1.7.7\r<br>	*	Apache 2.2.21\r<br>	*	MySQL 5.5.16 (Community Server)\r<br>	*	PHP 5.3.8 (VC9 X86 32bit thread safe) + PEAR\r<br>\r<br>================================================================================================', 3, 0, 10, '2012-01-31 11:02:03', '2012-02-01 00:57:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/110.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
