(116, 116, NULL, 'Added behavior.load to allow for a single go-to place to add/load javascript libraries. Also added jQuery plugin for loading jQuery library.', 'I have been working with Elin on a solution to add jQuery to Joomla to avoid multiple versions of jQuery running on a single site.\r<br>\r<br>My first commit: https://github.com/rcorral/joomla-cms/commit/47e208d8468851df3775205dc5bc6126ac55853d\r<br>With this I added a central place where javascript libraries can be registered with their css and js files.\r<br>An example of this would be doing this:\r<br>    JHtmlBehavior::register(''modal'', array(\r<br>      ''script'' => array(''system/modal.js'' => array()),\r<br>      ''stylesheet'' => array(''system/modal.css'' => array(array(), true, false, true))\r<br>      )\r<br>    );\r<br>\r<br>If more CSS or JS files need to be included, they can be added to the ''script'' or ''stylesheet'' array. For each element in the array the key is the path to the file, this file will get parsed by JHtml::_includeRelativeFiles, and the value for the key is an array of arguments that you would liked passed to JHtml::script or JHtml::stylesheet respectively.\r<br>\r<br>I modified JHtmlBehavior::modal as an example of how this new feature can be implemented. It makes a call to self::load(''modal''); to add the library to the document.\r<br>\r<br>With the second commit: https://github.com/rcorral/joomla-cms/commit/bf71fa00ede7620c67367ae05a5b3d6dc7b410c5\r<br>I added a Joomla plugin to register the jQuery library using the previous functions. It only registers the library if the plugin is enabled. It would be up to any Joomla extension to load it with the following code:\r<br>JHtml::_(''load'', ''jquery'');\r<br>\r<br>The reason for creating a plugin is to avoid all of the support that the Joomla team would have to do by supporting another JS library.\r<br>I think this is a great solution for a problem that many developers have been trying to overcome for years.\r<br>\r<br>Please review and comment.\r<br>\r<br>Cheers,\r<br>Rafael', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-02 18:36:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/116.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(117, 117, NULL, 'Christophe Demko mistake', 'http://joomlacode.org/gf/project/joomla/tracker/?action=TrackerItemEdit&tracker_id=8103&tracker_item_id=27872', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-03 08:53:43', '2012-02-05 10:53:30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/117.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(118, 118, NULL, 'Finder (Smart Search) plugins missing after upgrade to 2.5.1', 'I just upgraded my 1.7.3 site to 2.5.1 and noticed that Smart Search was missing from the Components menu. After some investigation I realized the plugin needed to be enabled in order for the component to show. I followed the following documentation to do so:\r<br>\r<br>http://docs.joomla.org/index.php?title=Smart_Search_quickstart_guide&oldid=64505\r<br>\r<br>Unfortunately, all the Smart Search plugins seem to be gone or were never installed upon upgrade. This may be due to the way I upgraded Joomla. I used the old method of extracting the Joomla update file, FTPing all the files and overwriting the old, I then logged into Joomla Admin and went to Extension Manager / Database / and clicked Fix. This seems to have worked in every regard, except Finder is not functioning (though I see it was installed via FTP under /components and /administrator/components.\r<br>\r<br>If I type the following I can see com_finder from my Joomla 2.5.1 Admin Panel:\r<br>\r<br>/administrator/index.php?option=com_finder\r<br>\r<br>Unfortunately, it is showing the following error on the page:\r<br>\r<br>Error loading component: com_finder, 1\r<br>Error loading component: com_finder, 1\r<br>\r<br>\r<br>So I am at a loss on how to get the plugins? Is there a download package? \r<br>\r<br>Also, let me explain why I had to upgrade Joomla the old fashioned way. For some reason when I went to Extension Manager / Update and attempted to upgrade to 2.5.1 it gave me the following error over and over again:\r<br>\r<br>JInstaller: :Install: Error SQL DB function failed with error number 1060\r<br>Duplicate column name ''sitename'' SQL=ALTER TABLE `jos_languages` ADD COLUMN `sitename` varchar(1024) NOT NULL AFTER `metadesc`;\r<br>SQL = ALTER TABLE `#__languages` ADD COLUMN `sitename` varchar(1024) NOT NULL AFTER `metadesc`;\r<br>Files Update: SQL error file DB function failed with error number 1060\r<br>Duplicate column name ''sitename'' SQL=ALTER TABLE `jos_languages` ADD COLUMN `sitename` varchar(1024) NOT NULL AFTER `metadesc`;\r<br>SQL = ALTER TABLE `#__languages` ADD COLUMN `sitename` varchar(1024) NOT NULL AFTER `metadesc`;\r<br> ', 3, 0, 10, '2012-02-04 17:57:50', '2012-02-05 18:36:56', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
