(120, 120, NULL, 'Update installer php version check error message from 1.7 to 2.5 closes #119', 'index.php of the installer contains a version check for php. In the event it fails an error message is displayed. This commit changes the Joomla version number from 1.7 to 2.5', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-05 15:57:58', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/120.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(121, 121, NULL, 'Finder / Smart Search Index Hangs on Large Content Sites', 'I have a #_content table of just about 3Gigs, 30k+ Articles and 4k+ Categories. In earlier versions of Finder before it was integrated into the latest release of Joomla 2.5 Stable I had the same problem I''m having now. It hangs and sometimes crashes my server requiring a Hard Reboot. I think this is due to having specific articles that are in pagebreak standards almost 400 book pages long. I have been building an online library using Joomla (which in retrospect may have been a bad idea, due to Joomla not really having the search functionality to deal with EXTREMELY large content based sites, and also that it uses MySQL which can be a huge bottleneck with large sites) and I have been letting the GUI Indexer run for about 9 hours now and it is hung up on 10% which was what happened earlier on in development when I tried this. I have used the CLI as well and let it run for 3 days and it never finished, and eventually shot up an error which ultimately nullified all the prior indexing.\r<br>\r<br>I have submit this issue to the Joomla! Bug Squad on Google Groups, yet it seems to have never been approved by a Moderator :(\r<br>\r<br>System Specs:\r<br>Rackspace Cloud Server\r<br>12 GIGS DDR3\r<br>PHP Built On 	Linux  2.6.18-238.19.1.el5xen #1 SMP Fri Jul 15 08:16:59 EDT 2011 x86_64\r<br>Database Version 	5.5.15\r<br>Database Collation 	utf8_general_ci\r<br>PHP Version 	5.3.8\r<br>Web Server 	Apache/2.2.3 (CentOS)\r<br>WebServer to PHP Interface 	cgi-fcgi\r<br>Joomla! Version 	Joomla! 2.5.1 Stable [ Ember ] 2-Feb-2012 14:00 GMT\r<br>Joomla! Platform Version 	Joomla Platform 11.4.0 Stable [ Brian Kernighan ] 03-Jan-2012 00:00 GMT ', 3, 0, 1, '2012-02-05 18:50:28', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
