(201, 201, NULL, 'Notice error with advanced seo and featured articles', 'If you activate the sef_advanced_link option (with a plugin or by temporary hardcode it in the router itself, see line 208) you get a notice error by following this steps:\r<br>\r<br>1. Use an empty Joomla! installation for the best test environment (so other menu links will not "fix" the bug)\r<br>2. Create a com_content article\r<br>3. Set the article as "featured"\r<br>4. Go to the default frontpage home link\r<br>5. Click on the article\r<br>6. Notice: Undefined index: id in components\\com_content\\router.php on line 278\r<br>7. Apply pull request\r<br>8. Check again\r<br>\r<br>Why do you get this notice error?\r<br>Because featured blog links have no "id" as request parameter.', 3, 0, 1, '2012-05-04 01:14:55', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/201.diff', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
